main event: Four objects, two large and two small, formed a rectangular pattern and proceeded from north to south at approximately 150 mph.
interesting points: The objects made sharp or zig-zag maneuvers., The sighting lasted for 45 minutes., Witness reported no other unusual activities at the time., The observer appeared competent and was described as very logical and coherent., The objects were too distant for the witness to estimate size and color.
sighted object: four flying objects arranged in a rectangular pattern
witness description: Observer's name was Mr. Williston; age and occupation unknown; described as logical and coherent.
